text: Necturus krausei is an extinct species of mudpuppy salamanders from the Paleocene of Saskatchewan in Canada. It is known from a set of vertebrae found in the Ravenscrag Formation. == References == Category:Proteidae Category:Prehistoric salamanders Category:Paleogene amphibians of North America Category:Paleogene Canada Category:Fossils of Canada Category:Paleontology in Saskatchewan Category:Fossil taxa described in 1978
